pr_description:
It is now possible to explicitly specify options for the fallback loader.

The `fallback` option now behaves similar to [`module.rules.use`](https://webpack.js.org/configuration/module/#rule-use).

This 1.0.1-based configuration…
``` javascript
{
  test: /\.(?:woff|woff2|eot|ttf|svg)$/,
  use: {
    loader: 'url-loader',
    options: {
      limit: 8192,
      fallback: 'file-loader'
    }
  }
}
```
…can now be written as
``` javascript
{
  test: /\.(?:woff|woff2|eot|ttf|svg)$/,
  use: {
    loader: 'url-loader',
    options: {
      limit: 8192,
      fallback: {
        loader: 'file-loader'
      }
    }
  }
}
```
And as one would expect, that means options can be provided, as well…
``` javascript
{
  test: /\.(?:woff|woff2|eot|ttf|svg)$/,
  use: {
    loader: 'url-loader',
    options: {
      limit: 8192,
      fallback: {
        loader: 'file-loader',
        options: {
          name: '[name].[ext]'
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Please look for potential to break existing configurations and surrounding loaders.

